sg roams 🇸🇬

25 Dec 2022 🎄✈️ Christmas looked a lil different this year. I spent a week in Bali (more from this mini trip later!) with my best friends after my 2 week stay in Singapore. Was able to see my parents one last time for a couple of hours before Cody and I flew back to LA on Christmas Day when they came to meet us during our transit through Singapore. That morning, I told my parents that Cody and I were down with food poisoning from our last day in Bali, and in response, they came to the airport armed with warm porridge, chicken rice if we felt up to it, juice, and birds nest, so we could have a meal that was gentle on our stomachs instead of having to eat the usual food at the airport. I wasn’t able to eat more than three bites of the food they brought because I felt so unwell but my heart was so full. I don’t deserve my parents. I already miss them so so much. It’s weird because the older I get, the harder it is for me to say bye to them at the airport. This trip back to Singapore meant a lot to me- it was the first trip back in years due to the pandemic + me being reluctant to leave LA due to work, and it was Cody’s first trip to Singapore to meet my family. Time flew by and I can’t believe it’s already over. Family truly means everything to me. I don’t say it often because it feels like I don’t deserve to say that since I don’t live with them and I am not there to share in whatever problems life brings, nor am I there to celebrate important things with them. But I love my family and I only hope I can give back to them someday. Will share more pics from both Singapore and Bali soon!!! Till next time ♥️🇸🇬 hope everyone is having the best best best holiday season no matter where you are in the world 🫶🏼🫶🏼🫶🏼

Nothing happy about what’s going on in the industry rn and having to go on strike but smiling while picketing because I’m proud to be a part of @sagaftra and happy we’re fighting for a fair contract for all actors + supporting WGA for theirs too! 

I know for most it’s very hard to understand everything that’s going on and why actors are striking when most of the actors you know and love are hollywood stars. But these big-named actors are actually just a tiny percentage of actors in SAG and hence, they are actually striking in solidarity with their fellow SAG-AFTRA members who are fighting for fair and more proportional pay under streaming guidelines, and protection against AI advancements.

87% of actors in SAG don’t make the minimum $26,470 annually to qualify for health insurance. Actors actors aren’t just the top stars of your fave tv shows and movies. We have to remember that every show/movie needs its background actors, guest stars, co-stars, stand-ins, body and stunt doubles, and more. These are all important roles. And the actors in these roles deserve to be paid fairly AND not have their likenesses taken at an outrageously small fee to be fed into AI and used forever without further compensation in order to save these big studios and networks even MORE money in addition to the billions they are already disproportionately earning off hardworking writers (the WGA is already on day 75 of picketing!!!!), actors, laborers, and crew members of all kinds. Which is why it’s so important we all stand together against big corporations now- when one union gets a fair contract, other unions in the industry and beyond are able to have more power to negotiate their contracts 💪🏼 #1u #sagaftrastrong #wgastrong

10 years with @codyhiroshi93 !!! 10 freaking years- from CHM151, to summer classes, to secret emails and waiting for each other at bus stops, to many sleepless nights at hayden library cramming for finals, to finishing each others essays, to tucson-living for a hot minute, to ldr almost killing us when I moved to LA, and to us doing life together here now, rediscovering our youth in our late 20s, going to bed early sometimes just to stay up till 3am talking about absolutely anything and everything. It’s not always perfect and I know I’m always crying and complaining about something, but I’m so lucky I found someone to trust; someone who believes in me and supports me like no other. You’ll probably never see this since you never use Instagram but I just wanted to tell the world how much I appreciate you and how much I fucking love you!! ♥️♥️♥️ (2nd pic was taken 10 years ago today!!!!!!!)
